<i>["If he loves you, he will stay and if not, he will leave."]</i>

33
00:05:07,200 --> 00:05:10,330
<i>["That's how relationships are, so don't stay attached to too many things." - Vivienne Westwood]</i>

34
00:05:14,920 --> 00:05:17,700
<i>[Now, We Are Breaking Up]</i>

35
00:05:19,340 --> 00:05:21,130
<i>[Episode 4]</i>

36
00:05:21,130 --> 00:05:22,060
<i>[Sonó]</i>

37
00:05:34,160 --> 00:05:37,830
Although they fought head-to-head with originality as the main weapon after copies surfaced,

38
00:05:37,830 --> 00:05:39,770
the results are tragic.

39
00:05:39,770 --> 00:05:42,310
It seems like they even got a top photographer, Mr. J,

40
00:05:42,310 --> 00:05:44,910
to try to make it up with a high-class image,

41
00:05:44,910 --> 00:05:47,040
but it did not influence the sales at all.

42
00:05:47,040 --> 00:05:50,630
Although Sonó is still at the top, it has started to fall from its peak.

43
00:05:50,630 --> 00:05:52,550
It's been stationary for two years.

44
00:05:52,550 --> 00:05:55,720
How is the store reorganization plan going?

45
00:05:56,490 --> 00:05:58,490
Here's the store reorganization plan.

46
00:05:58,490 --> 00:06:01,470
Some stores will be moved based on the revenue.

47
00:06:01,470 --> 00:06:03,130
<i>[Sonó]</i>

48
00:06:03,820 --> 00:06:06,090
Let's move the domestic brands including Sonó

49
00:06:06,090 --> 00:06:08,570
to the B zone on the third floor.

50
00:06:08,570 --> 00:06:11,880
Domestic brands no longer have competitive value.

51
00:06:11,880 --> 00:06:14,360
Chief Jeong, please re-do the reorganization of the stores

52
00:06:14,360 --> 00:06:17,610
focusing on the stores launching with foreign brands.

53
00:06:17,610 --> 00:06:19,440
That'll be all.

54
00:06:21,180 --> 00:06:22,810
Responsibility?

55
00:06:23,880 --> 00:06:27,100
Is this something that can be settled with a single page of written apology?

56
00:06:27,100 --> 00:06:29,900
We were on the second floor's A zone for eight years. Now we're on the third floor.

57
00:06:29,900 --> 00:06:32,090
And it's looking like we'll be pushed to the corner.

58
00:06:32,090 --> 00:06:34,700
Don't you know that a brand's power comes from its location in the department store?

59
00:06:34,700 --> 00:06:37,910
At this rate, it will only take a second for our reputation to turn sour.

60
00:06:37,910 --> 00:06:40,370
And like that, our brand could be shut down!

61
00:06:40,370 --> 00:06:42,480
Because you didn't want to lose.

62
00:06:42,480 --> 00:06:48,310
Take a good look at how much damage your stubbornness and misplaced bravado have caused.

63
00:06:49,750 --> 00:06:51,580
I'm sorry.

64
00:06:51,580 --> 00:06:54,240
This is not something that can be solved with an apology!

65
00:06:58,210 --> 00:06:59,960
I'm sorry.

66
00:07:06,740 --> 00:07:09,400
Anything going on with you these days?

67
00:07:09,400 --> 00:07:14,590
Me? Well, I'd like to find quickly a sense of security in life

68
00:07:14,590 --> 00:07:17,210
with a life-long partner of mine.

69
00:07:19,660 --> 00:07:21,740
It's not the first time we've had copies show up.

70
00:07:21,740 --> 00:07:24,990
Why are you wilted over such a matter? It's unlike you.

71
00:07:25,880 --> 00:07:27,590
Yes.

72
00:07:27,590 --> 00:07:31,060
You should observe your own daughter that carefully.

73
00:07:33,360 --> 00:07:36,580
There's nothing more foolish than holding onto what's already passed.

74
00:07:36,580 --> 00:07:38,320
Dust yourself off,

75
00:07:38,320 --> 00:07:43,000
and take your role in Clair Marie after getting a license with them.

76
00:07:45,550 --> 00:07:47,330
It's not a sudden decision that was made.

77
00:07:47,330 --> 00:07:51,430
Domestic brands have been overtaken by foreign brands at the department stores,

78
00:07:51,430 --> 00:07:53,940
and this is not a recent happening.

79
00:07:53,940 --> 00:07:55,950
We have to go with the times.

80
00:07:55,950 --> 00:07:57,470
Then what about Sonó?

81
00:07:57,470 --> 00:07:59,590
Why aren't you answering me?

82
00:08:00,650 --> 00:08:02,480
Yes, I understand.

83
00:08:02,480 --> 00:08:05,430
What about Sonó? What will you do with Sonó, Dad?

84
00:08:05,430 --> 00:08:08,400
Yeong Eun, explain it to her well.

85
00:08:10,390 --> 00:08:13,410
What is my dad saying?

86
00:08:13,410 --> 00:08:16,790
He's saying there is no foreign brand better than Clair Marie

87
00:08:16,790 --> 00:08:19,470
that appeals to Sonó's customer base.

88
00:08:19,470 --> 00:08:21,340
He's entrusted that matter to me.

89
00:08:21,340 --> 00:08:24,510
So, if you do that, what about Sonó?

90
00:08:26,100 --> 00:08:28,190
No way, is Sonó going to disappear?

91
00:08:28,190 --> 00:08:32,070
I have to go to our shop at The Hills to check on our display.

92
00:08:39,520 --> 00:08:41,980
If actress Han So Hye wears it, it will sell out.

93
00:08:41,980 --> 00:08:43,770
As the drama airs,

94
00:08:43,770 --> 00:08:48,170
we will promote the brand and price on blogs and social media.

95
00:08:48,170 --> 00:08:49,410
Okay.

96
00:08:50,220 --> 00:08:51,660
Episodes four and six.

97
00:08:51,660 --> 00:08:53,790
Did you confirm with the production company?

98
00:08:53,790 --> 00:08:56,250
The producer in charge has changed his number. Do you have it?

99
00:08:56,250 --> 00:08:58,080
Hold on.

100
00:08:59,720 --> 00:09:02,760
<i> Honey, can you buy me lunch?</i>

101
00:09:02,760 --> 00:09:05,000
<i>I want to eat dumplings.</i>

102
00:09:06,940 --> 00:09:10,690
CEO, how about we have lunch before we go back to the office?

103
00:09:10,690 --> 00:09:12,880
You can eat with Assistant Manager Seo and go in.

104
00:09:12,880 --> 00:09:15,100
I need to check some things still.

105
00:09:15,100 --> 00:09:18,010
- I'll see you in the office.
- Okay.

106
00:09:19,640 --> 00:09:23,300
I sent him three hearts for once, but this person really...

107
00:09:23,300 --> 00:09:26,010
<i>[Honey, can you buy me lunch? I want to eat dumplings.]</i>

108
00:09:34,320 --> 00:09:37,720
<i>Let's not pretend anymore.</i>

109
00:09:37,720 --> 00:09:39,600
<i>Why are you doing this?</i>

110
00:09:39,600 --> 00:09:45,510
<i>Let's not suppress the desire we have for each other any more.</i>

111
00:09:47,010 --> 00:09:50,930
<i> Wait, hold on.</i>

112
00:10:03,980 --> 00:10:07,540
Oh, Director Hwang Chi Sook, hello!

113
00:10:07,540 --> 00:10:11,140
I am here for my monthly meeting.

114
00:10:11,140 --> 00:10:13,360
What's with this energetic status report all of a sudden?

115
00:10:13,360 --> 00:10:15,690
Oh, well, goodbye.

116
00:10:15,690 --> 00:10:18,830
Why are you saying goodbye already? I've just started.

117
00:10:18,830 --> 00:10:20,350
What's the matter with you?

118
00:10:20,350 --> 00:10:22,490
We're at work!

119
00:10:23,780 --> 00:10:25,690
What are you doing?

120
00:10:25,690 --> 00:10:28,010
I was going to contact you anyway.

121
00:10:28,010 --> 00:10:30,750
I thought asking for understanding would be the right thing to do.

122
00:10:33,000 --> 00:10:36,820
Although it's kind of late for that,

123
00:10:36,820 --> 00:10:38,730
I completely understand.

124
00:10:38,730 --> 00:10:41,720
It's good manners for a virtuous man

125
00:10:41,720 --> 00:10:43,650
to not speak of what happened when we were drunk.

126
00:10:43,650 --> 00:10:45,640
Were you drinking already?

127
00:10:45,640 --> 00:10:47,070
What?

128
00:10:47,070 --> 00:10:49,060
I'd like to see Yoon Jae Gook.

129
00:10:49,060 --> 00:10:53,880
I thought apologizing to him personally for canceling the interview would be the right thing to do.

130
00:10:55,070 --> 00:10:56,770
Is that all?

131
00:10:56,770 --> 00:10:58,520
Does there need to be another reason?

132
00:10:58,520 --> 00:11:00,430
Do you go to a dermatologist frequently?

133
00:11:00,430 --> 00:11:02,130
It's one of my favorite places. Why?

134
00:11:02,130 --> 00:11:04,770
I was wondering if you ate some numbing cream, too.

135
00:11:04,770 --> 00:11:06,180
Are you playing twenty questions?

136
00:11:06,180 --> 00:11:08,670
If you don't remember, then never mind. Sure.

137
00:11:08,670 --> 00:11:12,440
Never mind. I'll let him know.

138
00:11:17,340 --> 00:11:19,250
I'm fine.

139
00:11:21,180 --> 00:11:24,120
I'm really fine. Really.

140
00:11:28,790 --> 00:11:32,140
Team Leader Ha Yeong Eun is doing well, right?

141
00:11:37,570 --> 00:11:39,430
You're staying longer than I expected.

142
00:11:39,430 --> 00:11:42,660
Yes. It turned out that way.

143
00:11:42,660 --> 00:11:45,850
- Why did you come find me?
- To ask for some work.

144
00:11:45,850 --> 00:11:50,810
I think I'm going to be staying here longer this time.

145
00:11:50,810 --> 00:11:53,230
Because of a woman?

146
00:11:53,230 --> 00:11:55,010
Yes.

147
00:12:01,580 --> 00:12:03,200
Who?

148
00:12:12,070 --> 00:12:15,320
Check with the manager which pieces to remove from the display.

149
00:12:15,320 --> 00:12:16,840
Also, we'll need to hang everything over again.

150
00:12:16,840 --> 00:12:19,090
Take lots of photos of the store meticulously beforehand.

151
00:12:19,090 --> 00:12:20,720
Okay.

152
00:12:27,740 --> 00:12:31,660
Na Ri, make sure you check with the manager which pieces to remove from the display.

153
00:12:31,660 --> 00:12:34,070
You just said that.

154
00:12:34,070 --> 00:12:37,430
- Are you okay?
- Yes, of course.

155
00:13:03,570 --> 00:13:06,490
The team leader is acting strange, right?

156
00:13:07,280 --> 00:13:09,870
The store is getting moved to the third floor,

157
00:13:09,870 --> 00:13:11,670
and the superiors are putting her in charge of licensing.

158
00:13:11,670 --> 00:13:13,790
Of course her mind's all over the place.

159
00:13:13,790 --> 00:13:16,260
It would be stranger for her not to be strange.

160
00:13:32,540 --> 00:13:36,130
Director Hwang said Team Leader Ha is doing well.

161
00:13:47,710 --> 00:13:51,070
Hey, cholesterol is an enemy to the middle-aged.

162
00:13:54,580 --> 00:13:58,330
But, our Cookie, why are you asking about Team Leader Ha's well-being?

163
00:13:58,330 --> 00:14:00,480
What's the reason?

164
00:14:00,480 --> 00:14:03,890
Yeah, Team Leader Ha is a good person.

165
00:14:03,890 --> 00:14:06,010
I've never heard of her dating anyone,

166
00:14:06,010 --> 00:14:09,190
and it has been seven or eight years since I've worked with her.

167
00:14:09,190 --> 00:14:13,360
How has our Cookie become so interested in such a hard-to-get woman?

168
00:14:13,360 --> 00:14:16,640
Hey. How about we eat separately from now on?

169
00:14:16,640 --> 00:14:20,630
The smell from that instant ramen... I really want to eat it.

170
00:14:20,630 --> 00:14:22,990
- About Sonó...
- What about Sonó?

171
00:14:22,990 --> 00:14:25,190
Are they going through a really hard time because of what happened with the copy?

172
00:14:25,190 --> 00:14:28,870
I'm sure it must be hard. It was definitely a blow.

173
00:14:28,870 --> 00:14:34,530
Oh, our Cookie is even worrying about her company now, huh?

174
00:14:34,530 --> 00:14:37,720
Why? Aren't you eating it?

175
00:14:37,720 --> 00:14:44,170
Hey. If a love cynic like you falls for someone, you know you'll suffer severely, right?

176
00:14:44,170 --> 00:14:45,980
Yes.

177
00:14:45,980 --> 00:14:48,920
But you can't do anything about your feelings?

178
00:14:48,920 --> 00:14:50,990
No.

179
00:14:50,990 --> 00:14:55,060
Your fast answers leave me with no doubt.

180
00:14:55,060 --> 00:14:56,650
I'm going to eat this.

181
00:14:56,650 --> 00:15:00,720
Food waste is a significant social issue.

182
00:15:05,390 --> 00:15:07,120
Yes, Mother?

183
00:15:07,120 --> 00:15:09,930
Ah, yes, Jae Gook is right next to me actually.

184
00:15:09,930 --> 00:15:14,170
Of course. Yes, hold on a second.

185
00:15:14,170 --> 00:15:16,150
Gosh, seriously?
<i>[Jae Gook's mother]</i>

186
00:15:21,850 --> 00:15:23,720
Yes?

187
00:15:23,720 --> 00:15:26,500
If you have time, stop by the house in the evening.

188
00:15:26,500 --> 00:15:28,590
I have something to tell you.

189
00:15:32,320 --> 00:15:34,530
Is it her son?

190
00:15:36,270 --> 00:15:39,030
Hey, you should be good to your mother.

191
00:15:39,030 --> 00:15:40,760
She even set up an arranged date for you.

192
00:15:40,760 --> 00:15:44,210
That kind of effort? I think it's love.

193
00:15:44,210 --> 00:15:45,920
When are you moving back home?

194
00:15:45,920 --> 00:15:48,640
It'll be the first time you'll be alone with your mom, right?

195
00:15:51,620 --> 00:15:53,660
I like you.

196
00:15:54,870 --> 00:15:58,130
If you're trying to say you're going to live with me, take it back.

197
00:15:58,130 --> 00:16:00,790
The heart does not move by will.

198
00:16:01,580 --> 00:16:03,500
Take care of me.

199
00:16:04,530 --> 00:16:07,820
Hey! A single cup of ramen is not good enough for what you're asking.

200
00:16:07,820 --> 00:16:09,760
Hey, Cookie!

201
00:16:23,770 --> 00:16:26,150
<i>Yoon Soo Wan.</i>

202
00:16:26,150 --> 00:16:31,930
<i>Does he really not mean anything to you?</i>

203
00:16:54,460 --> 00:16:56,560
Please be careful of its weight.

204
00:17:01,430 --> 00:17:05,160
- Is Team Leader Ha sick?
- Pardon?

205
00:17:06,740 --> 00:17:09,300
She has a lot going on lately.

206
00:17:09,300 --> 00:17:11,420
Can you give me the pin?

207
00:17:17,940 --> 00:17:19,560
<i>[Mi Sook]</i>

208
00:17:26,440 --> 00:17:30,870
Enjoy it! Unni, the dumplings just came out. Have some.

209
00:17:30,910 --> 00:17:33,790
Which will you have?

210
00:17:33,790 --> 00:17:36,810
I know it's been crazy for you after the copy surfaced,

211
00:17:36,810 --> 00:17:38,680
but you've been quite neglectful.

212
00:17:38,680 --> 00:17:41,800
How come you haven't called once?

213
00:17:41,800 --> 00:17:44,260
I've had a lot of work.

214
00:17:44,260 --> 00:17:47,310
Why'd you call me here suddenly?

215
00:17:47,310 --> 00:17:49,850
I really wanted to eat this all of a sudden.

216
00:17:49,850 --> 00:17:52,350
I was going to ask my husband,

217
00:17:52,350 --> 00:17:56,670
but he doesn't even reply to my texts nowadays.

218
00:17:56,670 --> 00:18:00,680
- Please enjoy.
- It's here! Let's eat, let's eat.

219
00:18:12,810 --> 00:18:15,030
Yes, this is it!

220
00:18:15,030 --> 00:18:19,090
It has been 10 years, yet the flavor hasn't changed one bit.

221
00:18:19,090 --> 00:18:23,510
The reason why I wanted to eat this suddenly...

222
00:18:24,730 --> 00:18:26,900
Never mind. I'll tell you once I know for sure.

223
00:18:26,900 --> 00:18:30,340
Just wait. You're going to know later today.

224
00:18:35,870 --> 00:18:37,590
What is it?

225
00:18:38,340 --> 00:18:40,020
Is it too hot?

226
00:18:47,300 --> 00:18:49,540
What's wrong?

227
00:18:49,540 --> 00:18:51,810
Did something happen?

228
00:18:55,560 --> 00:18:57,440
Mi Sook.

229
00:19:02,980 --> 00:19:06,400
I'm actually able to eat this.

230
00:19:08,270 --> 00:19:12,280
I'm able to eat dumplings.

231
00:19:12,980 --> 00:19:16,320
What is it? What happened?

232
00:19:18,900 --> 00:19:22,560
H-He died.

233
00:19:23,240 --> 00:19:24,990
Who?

234
00:19:29,480 --> 00:19:31,600
Soo Wan.

235
00:19:33,800 --> 00:19:38,420
That day, while he was on his way to me...

236
00:19:39,550 --> 00:19:41,480
he died.

237
00:19:50,270 --> 00:19:51,990
That terrible man.

238
00:19:51,990 --> 00:19:55,090
Why'd he die? How dare he die?

239
00:20:42,610 --> 00:20:45,250
I can order mine separately.

240
00:20:45,250 --> 00:20:49,090
I can't even eat much because my teeth get cold.

241
00:20:52,180 --> 00:20:55,270
We've studied together for two months now.

242
00:20:55,270 --> 00:20:58,690
I feel like we haven't talked much.

243
00:20:58,690 --> 00:21:02,420
Oh, but, how old are you?

244
00:21:02,990 --> 00:21:06,410
- What?
- I'm 67.

245
00:21:07,240 --> 00:21:10,630
I'm a year younger than you.

246
00:21:10,630 --> 00:21:13,860
Oh, at our age, being within 10 years apart makes us friends.

247
00:21:13,860 --> 00:21:16,050
You can speak informally to me.

248
00:21:17,650 --> 00:21:19,250
Here you go.

249
00:21:20,150 --> 00:21:24,680
Two years ago, my daughter spent a lot of money on me, and I had a dental implant.

250
00:21:24,680 --> 00:21:27,370
Thanks to her, I'm able to eat things like this.

251
00:21:27,370 --> 00:21:29,220
I see.

252
00:21:29,220 --> 00:21:34,550
Honestly, my husband and I haven't done much for her.

253
00:21:34,550 --> 00:21:40,260
My husband has always been in education, so he's not very worldly,

