00:41:42,880 --> 00:41:47,010
<i>That's our parents' problem. I don't care.</i>

496
00:41:48,090 --> 00:41:51,070
<i>My position is a little different, Jae Gook.</i>

497
00:41:51,070 --> 00:41:55,300
<i>If she loves you, she'll stay.
(in French)</i>

498
00:41:55,300 --> 00:41:58,490
<i>If she doesn't, she'll leave.
(in French)</i>

499
00:41:58,490 --> 00:42:04,880
<i>That's destiny. You can't really do anything about it.
(in French)</i>

500
00:42:05,940 --> 00:42:08,090
<i>Let her choose</i>

501
00:42:08,800 --> 00:42:10,990
<i>if you'll break up or not.</i>

502
00:42:12,740 --> 00:42:14,690
<i>You said you love her.</i>

503
00:42:17,760 --> 00:42:19,580
<i>You said you love her.</i>

504
00:42:33,420 --> 00:42:36,250
<i>[Yoon Soo Wan rests here forever]</i>

505
00:42:39,320 --> 00:42:43,780
Why did you tell me about Soo Wan?

506
00:42:43,780 --> 00:42:46,880
Because you don't seem like just a person whom I'll pass by in my life.

507
00:42:57,750 --> 00:43:00,960
It's love that ended in two months.

508
00:43:00,960 --> 00:43:05,790
Others might wonder what was so great about it,

509
00:43:05,790 --> 00:43:10,700
but time doesn't dictate the depth of love.

510
00:43:10,700 --> 00:43:15,200
For me at that time, those two months of time

511
00:43:15,200 --> 00:43:17,730
were significant enough to change my life.

512
00:43:17,730 --> 00:43:20,460
And it's time that's already passed.

513
00:43:20,460 --> 00:43:25,040
Let's not do anything from now on.

514
00:43:28,130 --> 00:43:32,620
I can't ignore that Soo Wan is your brother.

515
00:43:41,600 --> 00:43:44,370
Because your past is my brother...

516
00:43:46,350 --> 00:43:49,080
Is that the only reason why I can't be?

517
00:43:52,060 --> 00:43:55,970
I'm not confident about my choices.

518
00:43:55,970 --> 00:44:01,520
The one time that I chose with my heart and not my head

519
00:44:01,520 --> 00:44:03,600
was Soo Wan.

520
00:44:03,600 --> 00:44:07,770
And everything got messed up.

521
00:44:07,770 --> 00:44:10,130
I'm not my brother.

522
00:44:10,130 --> 00:44:14,390
And even if you make the same choices, the results might be different.

523
00:44:15,930 --> 00:44:17,740
Maybe

524
00:44:18,780 --> 00:44:21,480
if I were still 20,

525
00:44:21,480 --> 00:44:23,750
then it might have been.

526
00:44:23,750 --> 00:44:26,980
But I'm already 38,

527
00:44:26,980 --> 00:44:29,760
and there is no need for me to repeat misery.

528
00:44:33,180 --> 00:44:37,190
Experience is the coldest advice.

529
00:44:49,340 --> 00:44:52,460
Today, I came here with Yoon Soo Wan's younger brother,

530
00:44:52,460 --> 00:44:55,650
not with Yoon Jae Gook.

531
00:44:57,380 --> 00:44:59,600
Thank you.

532
00:44:59,600 --> 00:45:01,730
I'll go back by myself.

533
00:45:31,500 --> 00:45:34,450
<i>[The One]</i>

534
00:45:46,020 --> 00:45:48,330
<i>[The One]</i>

535
00:45:56,800 --> 00:45:58,690
You called to see me?

536
00:45:59,540 --> 00:46:02,730
Good morning, Noona. It's been a while.

537
00:46:03,770 --> 00:46:05,640
When did you get here?

538
00:46:05,640 --> 00:46:07,410
It's been two weeks since I got back.

539
00:46:07,410 --> 00:46:10,910
I successfully finished quarantining and got released yesterday.

540
00:46:10,910 --> 00:46:12,490
I told him to come back.

541
00:46:12,490 --> 00:46:14,960
Oh, okay.

542
00:46:15,880 --> 00:46:19,350
But the executive designer is still Director Hwang Chi Sook.

543
00:46:19,350 --> 00:46:23,420
How about we come out now? People who should know already know by now.

544
00:46:24,460 --> 00:46:27,120
Overall, her ideas have been actively reflected.

545
00:46:27,120 --> 00:46:29,770
Where? Where is it?

546
00:46:29,770 --> 00:46:32,120
I don't see any.

547
00:46:32,120 --> 00:46:35,190
Noona, why would you lie so professionally?

548
00:46:35,190 --> 00:46:38,250
If you're coming to work, correct how you call her.

549
00:46:39,170 --> 00:46:42,980
I still want freedom, but Dad approved of my condition

550
00:46:42,980 --> 00:46:44,900
that I work with you, Noona.

551
00:46:44,900 --> 00:46:48,110
Let's be together for good.

552
00:46:48,110 --> 00:46:50,780
I let that reckless guy loose for too long.

553
00:46:50,780 --> 00:46:52,510
I'm thinking about putting him in Clair Marie.

554
00:46:52,510 --> 00:46:55,540
Take him on and make sure you teach him well.

555
00:46:55,540 --> 00:46:57,010
Is it an official job?

556
00:46:57,010 --> 00:46:58,980
It is an official job.

557
00:47:03,800 --> 00:47:05,520
<i>[The One]</i>

558
00:47:07,220 --> 00:47:09,710
<i>Breaking news. All Hwang siblings made it in.</i>

559
00:47:09,710 --> 00:47:14,620
<i>He will be working under Team Leader Ha in the Clair Marie licensing team.</i>

560
00:47:14,620 --> 00:47:17,650
It's hard enough for her to take care of Director Hwang's matters,

561
00:47:17,650 --> 00:47:18,910
but now her brother's, too.

562
00:47:18,910 --> 00:47:23,050
It's like you've raised your first child and finally sent her off to school, then you get a second child.

563
00:47:24,220 --> 00:47:27,950
But then what happens to us?

564
00:47:29,820 --> 00:47:32,450
Say hello. This is Hwang Chi Hyeong.

565
00:47:32,450 --> 00:47:35,120
This is Manager Nam Na Ri, Assistant Manager Ahn Seon Joo,

566
00:47:35,120 --> 00:47:37,920
and Maknae* Jeong So Yeong of the design team.
<i>(Maknae means the youngest of the group)</i>

567
00:47:37,920 --> 00:47:40,960
Nice to meet you all.

568
00:47:43,130 --> 00:47:48,100
So... are we Sonó or Clair Marie licensing?

569
00:47:48,100 --> 00:47:52,000
I'd like to know what we're doing, Team Leader.

570
00:47:54,090 --> 00:47:56,460
<i>You'll go till the end with Sonó?</i>

571
00:47:56,460 --> 00:47:58,740
<i>It's a brand that I made with my own hands.</i>

572
00:47:58,740 --> 00:48:01,710
<i>I don't think it's right to put it in the storage </i>

573
00:48:01,710 --> 00:48:04,990
<i>because it has done its worth, then let someone else clean it up.</i>

574
00:48:04,990 --> 00:48:08,970
<i>If I have to take Chi Hyeong,</i>

575
00:48:08,970 --> 00:48:12,870
<i>I think he will have come to Sonó, not Clair Marie.</i>

576
00:48:15,860 --> 00:48:17,150
<i>Would it be alright?</i>

577
00:48:17,150 --> 00:48:20,160
It wasn't just my determination and tenacity.

578
00:48:20,160 --> 00:48:27,970
Sonó was my dream, my future, and my youth.

579
00:48:28,670 --> 00:48:30,520
We make clothes every season

580
00:48:30,520 --> 00:48:33,060
and our names are not on any of them,

581
00:48:33,060 --> 00:48:36,190
but they still mean something.

582
00:48:36,190 --> 00:48:38,870
So I should finish it up.

583
00:48:38,870 --> 00:48:40,690
Team Leader.

584
00:48:40,690 --> 00:48:44,340
Each one of you will have full say over your decision.

585
00:48:44,340 --> 00:48:46,750
So it's okay if you go to the license team.

586
00:48:46,750 --> 00:48:49,570
Sonó will only last two seasons at most anyway,

587
00:48:49,570 --> 00:48:51,790
and buying a license to place foreign brand labels

588
00:48:51,790 --> 00:48:56,500
on our clothes to increase sales is reality.

589
00:48:56,500 --> 00:48:59,990
It's fine. I'm staying, too.

590
00:48:59,990 --> 00:49:03,920
In college, I used to work part-time for months to buy one item of clothing from Sonó.

591
00:49:03,920 --> 00:49:07,990
And I got this job with the dream to make clothes like that.

592
00:49:09,390 --> 00:49:11,890
We'll be getting the least amount of marketing funds.

593
00:49:11,890 --> 00:49:13,510
And we'll be de-prioritized at the factory.

594
00:49:13,510 --> 00:49:16,590
They'll tell us to reduce the material fees.

595
00:49:16,590 --> 00:49:18,310
And we won't even be able to dream about Italian fabric.

596
00:49:18,310 --> 00:49:21,070
With all that, the number of stores will decrease,

597
00:49:21,070 --> 00:49:23,860
and we'll end up at outlets later on.

598
00:49:23,860 --> 00:49:26,120
But instead, we can do anything, right?

599
00:49:26,120 --> 00:49:27,690
There are so many things I couldn't try.

600
00:49:27,690 --> 00:49:29,490
It's a brand they're getting rid of anyway.

601
00:49:29,490 --> 00:49:31,530
We won't have to worry about sales anymore.

602
00:49:31,530 --> 00:49:33,320
We won't have to worry about what the higher-ups will say.

603
00:49:33,320 --> 00:49:38,890
Can I make whatever I want for the remaining seasons?

604
00:49:39,820 --> 00:49:41,440
I'll stay too.

605
00:49:41,440 --> 00:49:43,360
Except let me have a chance at designing a matching set.

606
00:49:43,360 --> 00:49:45,280
Instead of switching jobs in between skill levels,

607
00:49:45,280 --> 00:49:47,780
I want to gain more experience here before I leave.

608
00:49:50,040 --> 00:49:52,810
Hey, Maknae over there.

609
00:49:53,730 --> 00:49:55,860
Sorry? Are you calling me?

610
00:49:55,860 --> 00:49:58,490
I'll be your mentor from now on.

611
00:49:58,490 --> 00:50:01,110
Is that okay, Team Leader?

612
00:50:01,110 --> 00:50:02,550
How much do you know about fabric?

613
00:50:02,550 --> 00:50:04,590
Oh, fabric?

614
00:50:04,590 --> 00:50:06,430
I don't really know anything about fabric,

615
00:50:06,430 --> 00:50:09,580
but I do know popular shops.

616
00:50:11,330 --> 00:50:14,480
I'm going out for a meeting regarding material parts.

617
00:50:14,480 --> 00:50:16,210
Alright.

618
00:50:34,710 --> 00:50:36,870
<i>But, Mi Sook...</i>

619
00:50:39,040 --> 00:50:41,170
<i> You know what?</i>

620
00:50:41,170 --> 00:50:43,590
<i> To be honest, when I found out,</i>

621
00:50:46,090 --> 00:50:48,650
<i> I asked myself,</i>

622
00:50:48,650 --> 00:50:50,870
<i> "What should I do?"</i>

623
00:50:50,870 --> 00:50:53,030
<i> That person was saying</i>

624
00:50:53,890 --> 00:50:56,780
<i> Soo Wan was his older brother.</i>

625
00:50:57,700 --> 00:51:01,730
<i>But I was asking myself,</i>

626
00:51:02,920 --> 00:51:04,880
<i> "What should I do with him?"</i>

627
00:51:10,210 --> 00:51:13,520
<i>What should I do?</i>

628
00:51:19,140 --> 00:51:21,880
What else can I do? It turned out for the better.

629
00:51:21,880 --> 00:51:24,150
This is good enough.

630
00:51:24,150 --> 00:51:26,670
You did well, Ha Yeong Eun.

631
00:52:23,360 --> 00:52:25,890
What we'll do in the future...

632
00:52:27,020 --> 00:52:29,680
Whether or not we'll continue to meet ...

633
00:52:30,490 --> 00:52:32,260
Yes,

634
00:52:33,130 --> 00:52:35,760
that's all up to you.

635
00:52:35,760 --> 00:52:37,540
But...

636
00:52:41,860 --> 00:52:44,100
Tell me this one thing.

637
00:52:48,300 --> 00:52:49,870
Did you...

638
00:52:52,390 --> 00:52:54,320
miss me?

639
00:53:03,670 --> 00:53:07,160
<i>From where should I start telling her my story?</i>

640
00:53:16,390 --> 00:53:21,790
<i>[It is my pleasure to recommend Ha Yeong Eun to this program...]</i>

641
00:53:22,730 --> 00:53:25,180
<i>Yes, I'll be leaving now.
(in French)</i>

642
00:53:25,180 --> 00:53:27,500
<i>What will you do with the recommendation letter
(in French)</i>

643
00:53:27,500 --> 00:53:30,370
<i>for the student that Levain is supporting right now?
(in French)</i>

644
00:53:30,370 --> 00:53:32,180
<i> You can just write it yourself.
(in French)</i>

645
00:53:32,180 --> 00:53:33,780
<i>Me?
(in French)</i>

646
00:53:34,790 --> 00:53:36,710
<i>What should I write?
(in French)</i>

647
00:53:36,710 --> 00:53:39,850
<i>Come on! You don't expect me to take care of that too, do you?
(in French)</i>

648
00:53:39,850 --> 00:53:42,650
<i>I have thousands of things to do before the shoot.
(in French)</i>

649
00:53:42,650 --> 00:53:45,860
<i>Just write something and get here already!
(in French)</i>

650
00:53:45,860 --> 00:53:48,060
<i>You're driving me nuts!
(in French)</i>

651
00:54:06,110 --> 00:54:09,480
<i>[I hope one day your passion]</i>

652
00:54:12,490 --> 00:54:15,090
<i>[I hope one day your passion becomes a "sonó."]</i>

653
00:54:22,730 --> 00:54:25,180
<i>You haven't left yet? You said you have a shoot today.</i>

654
00:54:25,180 --> 00:54:27,690
<i> Yeah, I have to leave now, but...</i>

655
00:54:32,340 --> 00:54:36,720
<i>This... Can you deliver it to her for me?</i>

656
00:54:36,720 --> 00:54:39,120
<i> The school and name are all written on there.</i>

657
00:54:39,120 --> 00:54:42,050
<i> - Thanks a lot.
- Sure.</i>

658
00:54:46,880 --> 00:54:48,830
<i> Don't be late and get it to her on time.</i>

659
00:54:48,830 --> 00:54:51,980
<i> It's really important for that student. Okay?</i>

660
00:54:51,980 --> 00:54:53,620
<i> Alright. You can get going quickly.</i>

661
00:54:53,620 --> 00:54:55,330
<i>Thank you.
(in French)</i>

662
00:54:59,960 --> 00:55:02,980
<i>[I hope one day your passion becomes a "sonó."]</i>

663
00:55:02,980 --> 00:55:05,690
<i>Who took my pins holder?
(in French)</i>

664
00:55:05,690 --> 00:55:07,810
<i>Ah, thank you.
(in French)</i>

665
00:55:19,070 --> 00:55:22,180
<i>- What are you looking for?
- Who moved the lace? (in French)</i>

666
00:55:22,180 --> 00:55:23,890
<i>Excuse me.</i>

667
00:55:23,890 --> 00:55:28,260
<i>I'm looking for someone. She's named Ha Yeong Eun.</i>

668
00:55:28,260 --> 00:55:29,700
<i>I'm not understanding you.
(in French)</i>

669
00:55:29,700 --> 00:55:32,930
<i>Ha Yeong Eun.</i>

670
00:55:32,930 --> 00:55:36,110
<i>Ha Yeong Eun... is right here.</i>

671
00:55:44,260 --> 00:55:45,960
<i>Hello.</i>

672
00:55:47,310 --> 00:55:49,400
<i>I'm Yoon Soo Wan.</i>

673
00:55:53,770 --> 00:55:55,800
<i>[Portfolio]
[YEH]</i>

674
00:55:59,640 --> 00:56:04,980
<i> From where did our start go awry?</i>

675
00:56:07,390 --> 00:56:09,760
<i>Come look! Come look!
(in French)</i>

676
00:56:09,760 --> 00:56:11,950
<i>They're photos of Paris.
(in French).</i>

677
00:56:34,290 --> 00:56:36,370
<i>How much?
(in French).</i>

678
00:56:48,040 --> 00:56:51,510
<i>Someone bought that? Who?</i>
<i>(in French)</i>

679
00:56:51,510 --> 00:56:53,340
<i>Some girl.</i>
<i>(in French)</i>

680
00:57:04,310 --> 00:57:09,610
<i> How many times</i>

681
00:57:09,610 --> 00:57:12,090
<i> have we passed by each other?</i>

682
00:57:21,670 --> 00:57:25,800
<i>By chance, is it Ha Yeong Eun?</i>

683
00:57:27,770 --> 00:57:32,630
<i>- Jae Gook.
- Noona, I know what you want to say.</i>

684
00:57:32,630 --> 00:57:36,880
<i> My brother isn't here anymore.</i>

685
00:57:38,850 --> 00:57:43,470
<i> How much time</i>

686
00:57:43,470 --> 00:57:46,030
<i>passed by while we missed each other until we finally met?</i>

687
00:57:46,660 --> 00:57:49,040
<i>But none of that matters.</i>

688
00:57:49,760 --> 00:57:52,120
<i> Just this one thing.</i>

689
00:57:52,120 --> 00:57:54,300
Tell me this one thing.

690
00:57:57,270 --> 00:57:58,900
Did you...

691
00:58:01,290 --> 00:58:03,340
miss me?

692
00:58:08,030 --> 00:58:09,970
I...

693
00:58:12,210 --> 00:58:14,110
missed you.

694
00:58:21,080 --> 00:58:28,230
♫ <i>Both the season of youth and the warm wind</i> ♫

695
00:58:28,230 --> 00:58:33,530
♫ <i>Don't mean anything</i> ♫

696
00:58:33,530 --> 00:58:37,150
♫ <i>Because you're not here</i> ♫

697
00:58:37,150 --> 00:58:41,210
♫ <i>To clear my head</i> ♫

698
00:58:41,210 --> 00:58:47,730
♫ <i>When I keep aimlessly wandering the streets</i> ♫

699
00:58:47,730 --> 00:58:56,990
♫ <i>Without being aware, I'm here in front of your house</i> ♫

700
00:58:58,390 --> 00:59:04,960
♫ <i>Should I call you</i> ♫

701
00:59:04,960 --> 00:59:12,410
♫ <i>After looking for your name with trembling hands</i> ♫

702
00:59:12,410 --> 00:59:14,920
♫ <i>I put the phone back down</i> ♫

703
00:59:14,920 --> 00:59:17,890
<i>[Now, We Are Breaking Up Preview]</i>

704
00:59:17,890 --> 00:59:21,960
<i> - Are you thinking about doing something new?
- Let's do it in a classic style, how Sonó should be.</i>

705
00:59:21,960 --> 00:59:25,300
<i>- Don't touch that.
- It's not like we're machines. We need at least a month.</i>

706
00:59:25,300 --> 00:59:26,590
<i>Those are going to Clair Marie though.</i>

707
00:59:26,590 --> 00:59:28,130
<i> I won't go easy on you from now on.</i>

708
00:59:28,130 --> 00:59:29,950
<i>So on your own, try to beat me with your abilities.</i>

709
00:59:29,950 --> 00:59:33,030
<i> Can I actually? Is it really okay for me to beat you?</i>

710
00:59:33,030 --> 00:59:35,400
<i> Cookie, a job finally came in for you.</i>

711
00:59:35,400 --> 00:59:39,950
<i>Mr. J has agreed to collaborate with us.</i>

712
00:59:40,750 --> 00:59:42,120
<i> I just have to send it over by tomorrow, right?</i>

713
00:59:42,120 --> 00:59:45,190
<i>I'm worried he will lose all of his retirement savings from his interest in investing.</i>

714
00:59:45,190 --> 00:59:47,470
<i> It's not like I have two or three kids.</i>

715
00:59:47,470 --> 00:59:50,670
<i>I told you to go to your dad, didn't I?</i>

716
00:59:50,670 --> 00:59:54,320
<i>- Dad.
- But do you two know each other?</i>

717
00:59:54,320 --> 00:59:55,280
<i>- No.
- Yes.</i>

718
00:59:55,280 --> 00:59:56,990
<i> - Excuse me.
- But who is the person in there?</i>

719
00:59:56,990 --> 00:59:59,490
<i> He's the photographer collaborating with Clair Marie.</i>

720
00:59:59,490 --> 01:00:02,760
<i> - Jae Gook!
- I don't want to fuss over things that happened in the past.</i>

721
01:00:02,760 --> 01:00:04,740
<i>The future is more important.</i>

722
01:00:04,740 --> 01:00:08,480
<i> I already have a woman I'd like to be a man for.</i>

723
01:00:08,480 --> 01:00:10,550
<i>Jae Gook has a woman he likes.
[Wedding invitation: Soo Wan, Yoo Jeong]</i>

724
01:00:10,550 --> 01:00:12,660
<i> Have you met her?</i>

725
01:00:12,660 --> 01:00:15,150
<i>It's the first time he's talked about a woman like that.</i>

726
01:00:15,150 --> 01:00:19,420
<i> You should change your background now.</i>

727
01:00:21,140 --> 01:00:24,730
♫ <i>My departing footsteps are heavy</i> ♫
